      "content": "That makes sense, but I need to see it in action to know if the rhythm is right. Could you actually write out a short scene? Maybe three or four characters—local business owners or politicians—sitting in a wood-paneled office. I want the dialogue to be unvarnished. Instead of just saying they want \"order,\" show me how they would actually describe the people they're worried about and the \"threats\" they feel are coming to their town. I need the grit and the real, uncomfortable mindset of that specific time and place to make the book feel real.",
